For convenience, the key requirements of AGPL-3.0:

  1. You may copy, distribute and modify the software under the same license.
  2. If you modify the software and let users interact with it over a network
     (e.g. host it on a website), you MUST make your modified source code
     available to those users under AGPL-3.0. (This is the "Affero" clause
     that GPL lacks — it closes the SaaS loophole.)
  3. You must preserve copyright and license notices.

